DESIGN PATTERNS:
- A group of 4 people introduced 23 design patterns to solve the common problems in software development.
(All these patterns follows SOLID principle)

Types:

1.Creational - 5
- It handle on object creation 
- It inculdes Singleton,Factory,Abstract Factory,Builder,Prototype

2.Structural - 7
- It focus on how classes and objects are composed to form larger structures.
- It includes Adapter,Bridge,Composite,Decorator,Facade,Flyweight,Proxy

3.Behavioral - 11
- It focus on how the object behave (like how they are communicated and their responsiblities)
- It includes Observer,Strategy,Command,Chain of Responsibility,State,Iterator,Mediator,Memento,Template Method,Visitor,Interpreter
